The Special Adviser to President Muhammadu Buhari on the Niger Delta, ‎Prof Charles Quaker Dokubo, has called on leaders in the oil rich region to support the president’s reelection bid. Dokubo, who is also the coordinator of the Presidential Amnesty Programme (PAP), urged all the people of the Niger Delta to ensure that ‎the current peace enjoyed in the region was maintained. He said ‎this during a visit to a Niger Delta activist and peace advocate, Chief Mike Ekayama Loyibo. He said the region had a lot to benefit from the current peace and the president’s reelection come 2019. Dokubo, in a statement in Abuja, said the Presidential Amnesty Programme was at a critical stage and needed the support of all patriotic and peace-loving Niger Deltans for it to achieve the desired results.